<br>
Personally, I'd say that if a) members are donating to the board for its status, then there should be some say as to what goes on. I dont know who is paying for it at this time, however.<br>
<br>
b) If the admins want absolute control, get off of ezboard asap and find someone that can run pHp boards. Ezboard is more of a capitalist pig than anything I've ever seen, prompting many guilds to change to personal web boards.<br>
<br>
I think the crux of the issue (from an impartial side) is that you have persons paying for their posting status, and then being told essentially they cannot post in a forum that technically should be anything goes. Now..from an admin pov, posts = money they have to pay out, hence their wishing to cut down on the pointless drabble as well. It's a catch 22. Solution once again would be to migrate to another forum of sorts. I know when I moved from Ezboard to www.vbulletin.com...they had a script and an admin that transferred all of the existing posts in ezboard so you lose nothing..and of course this forum would still be a library.<br>
<br>
Cost...sure its steep *initially*...$160 for owning it. But after that its only 30 / yr for software updates etc...well worth it in the long run.<br>
<br>
